Hoya Order Creation Process
Step 1: Configure Shipping Method

Go to:
Sales → Configuration → Sales Orders → Shipping Methods

Open or create the shipping method:
“Eshop Connector”

Configure the following fields:

Eshop Carrier Code: DPD

Is Express Carrier: ✅ True (Boolean)

The carrier must be included in the payload as:

"carrier": {
    "key": "DPD"
}

===============================================

Step 2: SCAYLE Order – RX + Express Condition

If a SCAYLE order meets both conditions:

Order type is RX

Delivery method is Express

Then:

A new boolean field “Consider Manual” will automatically be set to True on the Zeiss order.

To Verify:

Open the SCAYLE order.

Open the related Zeiss order.

Confirm:

Consider Manual: ✅ True

==================================================

Step 3: Email Configuration (Hoya Email State)

Go to:
Settings → Technical → Email → Emails

Check the Hoya email send state to ensure the email has been processed correctly.

=====================================================

Step 4: System Parameter Configuration

Navigate to:
Settings → Technical → Parameters → System Parameters

A system parameter must be configured:

Key: hoya_manual_order.default_product_tmpl_id

Value: 107

This parameter defines the default product template ID used for processing manual Hoya orders.

=====================================================

Step 5: Manual Hoya Order Creation

Click on Manual Hoya Order.

In the wizard, the Order Type field provides two options:

🔹 Stock

The SD Order ID will:

Be auto-generated (8-digit number)

Be read-only

🔹 Cross-dock

The user must manually enter the SD Order ID.

